sentences: Hernán Raúl Núñez Oyarce (July 4, 1914 – December 4, 2005), also known as Nano Núñez, was a cuequero musician and composer.
The following year, they recorded the album, La cueca brava, with the addition of accordionist Carlos "Pollito" Navarro.
In 1998, Núñez became the 12th artist to receive the designation as one of the fundamental figures of Chilean music.
